FlashAttention prefill+decode landed (tsk-22 done)

Status: COMPLETED at commit 7771ea3.

rocm_attn_fa_kernel added as drop-in for rocm_attn_batch_kernel on the
non-topk paths.  One block per (Q-tile, head); BR=4 Q rows per block, one
wave (32 lanes) per row.  Sink baked in as virtual first key.  K and V
share cooperative LDS load (MLA path: raw_kv and comp_kv each serve as
both K and V).

Validation:
  - 40 oracle tests pass
  - canonical 21-tok benchmark: 29.62 / 29.75 / 29.71 t/s prefill (3 runs),
    decode 13.61 t/s -- flat vs 29.17 baseline

The gain is structural (constant LDS, no n_keys-sized scratch, BR-fold
fewer K/V reads).  At 21 prefill tokens, attention is too small a slice
(~3% of histogram) for the win to show.  At longer prefill / chunked
prefill, gains will compound.

Non-FA paths preserved:
  - use_topk: legacy kernel still handles indexed_mixed_batch
  - head_dim not divisible by 32: legacy kernel handles

Next lever: codex query running for ranked recommendations; expect MoE
expert-major regrouping for prefill or HIP graph capture (tsk-16/20) to
be the next-biggest win.

